quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  8,53,"That is because Allah is not one to change the favour He has bestowed on a people, until they first change what they have in themselves (in their own souls), and because Allah is Hearer and Knower"
  8,54,"Their way is like those of Pharaoh´s people and those before them! They denied Our Signs (or revelations), and We destroyed them in their sins, and drowned Pharaoh´s people. All were evildoers"
  8,55,"Verily, the worst of beasts in Allah´s eyes are those who are ungrateful and will not believe"
  8,56,"Those with whom if you make a treaty, they break their treaty at each opportunity, for they fear not (or keep not their duty to) Allah"
  8,57,"Should you come to war with them, then deal with them so as to strike fear into those who come after them (as an example), that per chance (or possibly) they may remember"
  8,58,"And should you ever fear treachery from any people, then throw back to them their treaty in like manner (or in fairness); verily, Allah loves not the treacherous"
  8,59,"Let not those who disbelieve deem that they can outstrip (believers or Allah´s purpose); verily, they cannot frustrate them (or escape)"
  8,60,"Prepare you against them what strength of forces and horses you have to the utmost of your power, that thereby you may dismay the enemies of Allah, and your enemies, and others beside them whom you know not. You do not know them, but Allah knows them! Wha"
  8,61,"But if they incline to peace, incline you to it also, and trust in Allah; verily, He is Hearer and Knower"